Rockers Bon Jovi are making a stop at Tampa’s Amalie Arena on April 15. As part of their tour, simply called 2022, the band is giving local acts the chance to open for them. Bands are encouraged to submit an audition video of original music to bonjovi.com/openingact. One local band will be selected for each tour date. Tampa Bay rockers, post your video and make us proud — we’ll be livin’ on a prayer to see who gets chosen. The Bon Jovi 2022 tour is produced by Live Nation. Tickets range from $15.75 to $746.25 and are on sale now at ticketmaster.com.